{
  "stem": "18061.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we had synagogues, beautiful synagogues.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One of the most beautiful was the-- we called it the German synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's-- that's the name was all the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Where for holiday, at that time, people used to come with horses and wagon-- [INAUDIBLE] beautiful wagon.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] they called it-- to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "High cylinder hats.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Very, very rich, very famous people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, today, they make, from that synagogue, a museum, and also a opera house from that right now.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, in-- in Czenstochowa, same place.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then we had a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They called it the old synagogue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The old synagogue was for people, common people, not the very rich, not the very poor.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Over there, we had special canters.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was make something, something like a dream.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I got a friend of mine, which I will talk about him later, who was with me in Treblinka, his father painted it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He took eight years.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Not just painting.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "No, the pictures created on the ceiling and on the walls, they were masterpieces.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, it was destroyed in the first days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had institution to help poor people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had doctors.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Somebody was sick, they went to, didn't have to pay anything, with medicine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had institution like very, very poor people, they couldn't afford to make a meal out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we had an institution that supported them, that brought in food for them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had also an institution to marry off young girls, which they had no diary-- dowry.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they took-- I don't know from where-- and they clothed them, and they married them off, which call, in our language, Hachnasat Cala, to bring in the [? caller ?] that she shouldn't be ashamed, as your married.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
